.SH Version 2.0.0 (2013\-05\-05)
.PP
This release renames md2man executables and libraries to highlight the fact
that md2man provides two processing pathways: one for Roff and one for HTML.
.PP
Major:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Rename 
.BR md2man (1) 
executable to 
.BR md2man-roff (1).
.IP \(bu 2
Rename \fB\fCMd2Man::Engine\fR to \fB\fCMd2Man::Roff::Engine\fR\&.
.IP \(bu 2
Rename "manpage\-reference" CSS class to "md2man\-xref" in HTML output.
.IP \(bu 2
The \fB\fCMd2Man::Document#reference()\fR method now takes only two parameters:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\fCinput_match\fR \- MatchData object for the reference in Markdown input
containing the following named capture groups:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\fC:page\fR \- name of the manual page
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\fC:section\fR \- section number of the manual page
.RE
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\fCoutput_match\fR \- MatchData object for the reference in output document
containing the following named capture groups:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\fC:addendum\fR \- non\-space characters immediately after the reference in
the output document
.RE
.RE
.RE
.PP
Patch:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Prevent cross\-references from being expanded inside HTML tags.
.RE
.PP
Other:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Add 
.BR md2man (5) 
manual page detailing md2man's markdown file format.
.RE
